          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Independent yields of Rh-102m,Rh-102g and Rh-101g",
                " for thermal-neutron-induced fission of U-235."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERMUN"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Munich research reactor."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " In the core of Munich research reactor.",
                " Average thermal neutron flux and equivalent fission",
                " flux were 2.0 x 10**13 and 4.0 x 10**12 n/cm**2/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " U-235 sample consisted of two small fuel plates.",
                " Each was composed of Al-U alloy containing 1.45 gr",
                " of metallic U enriched to 92.81% U-235.",
                " Rhodium metal, to measure the amount of Rh-102m,g",
                " by Rh-103(n,2n) reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiated for 358 hr."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI",
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A coaxial Ge(Li) detector with a 16.9%",
                " photopeak efficiency relative to a 3x3 in. NaI(Tl)",
                " crystal and a resolution of 2.1 keV for 1.33 MeV",
                " gamma-ray of Co-60. The detector was set up in a 20",
                " cm thick lead cave."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence correction by comparing the photopeak",
                " efficiencies of the detector for the measured gamma-",
                " transition of a Rh-102m,g standard source.",
                " Contributions from Rh-103(n,2n)Rh-102."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
